	<p style="text-align:center"><strong>Bad  Girls Club VIP Sweepstakes</strong><br>
		<strong>Official Rules</strong><br>
		<strong>September  26, 2011—November 8, 2011</strong></p>
	<p><strong>PRELIMINARY INFORMATION:  </strong>NO PURCHASE NECESSARY. A purchase will  not improve your chances of winning. Void where prohibited. The Bad Girls Club VIP Sweepstakes  (&ldquo;Sweepstakes&rdquo;) will begin on  September 26, 2011 at 12:01 A.M. ET and end on November 8, 2011 at 1:00 A.M. ET  (&ldquo;Sweepstakes Period&rdquo;).  All times in the  Sweepstakes refer to Eastern Time (&ldquo;ET&rdquo;). Odds of winning depend upon  the number of eligible Entries (as defined below) received.  Sweepstakes is subject to all applicable  federal, state and local laws.</p>
	<p><strong>ELIGIBILITY:</strong> Open only to permanent,  legal United States (&ldquo;U.S.&rdquo;) residents who are physically residing in one (1)  of the fifty (50) U.S. or the District of Columbia (excluding Puerto Rico,  Guam, the U.S. Virgin Islands and other U.S. territories), and who are eighteen  (18) years of age or older as of the start of the Sweepstakes Period.   Officers, directors, and employees of Sweepstakes Entities (as defined  below), members of these persons&rsquo; immediate families (spouses and/or parents,  children, and siblings, and their spouses, regardless of where they reside),  and/or persons living in the same households as these persons (whether or not  related thereto) are not eligible to enter or win the Sweepstakes.  Sweepstakes Entities, as referenced herein,  shall include Oxygen Media LLC, 75 9th Ave, New York, NY  10011, NBCUniversal Media, LLC, 30 Rockefeller Plaza, New York, NY 10112,  (collectively, &ldquo;Sponsors&rdquo;), and their  respective parent, subsidiary, and affiliate companies, and their administrative, advertising, and promotion agencies, and any other entity  involved in the development, administration, promotion, or implementation of  the Sweepstakes.</p>
	<p><strong>TO ENTER:</strong> To  enter the Sweepstakes during the Sweepstakes Period, you must be a registered  member of <a href="http://www.meebo.com">www.meebo.com</a>. To become a  registered member, visit www.meebo.com and follow the provided instructions to  register for free. Please note that registration for and use of www.meebo.com  is subject to Meebo&rsquo;s Privacy Policy (https://www.meebo.com/privacy/full/).  Once registered for <a href="http://www.meebo.com/">www.meebo.com</a>, visit  the Oxygen Bad Girls Club website at <u>bad-girls-club.oxygen.com</u> (the &ldquo;Website&rdquo;), and &ldquo;check-in&rdquo; by using the Meebo toolbar (&ldquo;Check-In&rdquo;)  and then follow the provided instructions to complete and thereafter submit the  entry form, which includes your name, city, state,  e-mail address, and date of birth (&ldquo;Entry&rdquo;).  All Entries become the property of Sponsors, and will not be acknowledged.  Each  Check-In will be deemed one (1) Entry into the Sweepstakes.</p>
	<p><strong>Entries for each Weekly Drawing  must be received before end date specified in chart below. Entries for the last  Weekly Drawing (Weekly Drawing 6) must be received before November 8, 2011 at  1:00 A.M. ET to be eligible for the Sweepstakes.</strong> <strong>Limit seven (7) Entries per  person per Weekly Entry Period for a maximum of forty-two (42) entries for the  entire Sweepstakes Period. </strong>Entries  received from any person or email address beyond this limit will void all such  additional Entries. Entries generated by a script, macro, or other  automated means will be disqualified.<strong>  </strong>Entries  that are incomplete, garbled, corrupted, or unintelligible for any reason,  including, but not limited to, computer or network malfunction or congestion, are void and will not be accepted.  In case of a dispute over the identity of an entrant, the  authorized account holder of the email address used to enter will be deemed to  be the entrant. &ldquo;Authorized account holder&rdquo; is defined as the person who is  assigned to an email address by an Internet access provider, online service  provider or other organization that is responsible for assigning email  addresses for the domain associated with the submitted email address.&nbsp; Entry constitutes permission (except where prohibited by  law) to use entrant&rsquo;s name, city, state, likeness, image, and/or voice for  purposes of advertising, promotion, and publicity in any and all media now or hereafter  known, throughout the world in perpetuity, without additional compensation,  notification, permission, or approval.  <strong></strong></p>
